g.title: Sheet.3334
g.desc: A client sends a request to the proxy instead of directly to ...
g.text: A client sends a request to the proxy instead of directly to the destination. This can happen because the client PC is configured to use the proxy, or because the network redirects traffic to the proxy (transparent proxy).

g.title: Sheet.3335
g.desc: The proxy checks the request. It may consult policy, cache, o...
g.text: The proxy checks the request. It may consult policy, cache, or authentication services. If the request is valid and allowed, the proxy opens a connection to the destination server.

g.title: Sheet.3336
g.desc: When the server responds, the proxy can inspect or modify the...
g.text: When the server responds, the proxy can inspect or modify the response. The proxy then sends the final response back to the client.
